Privacy Policy for Travooz
Last Updated: 12/11/2025
Introduction
Welcome to Travooz. Your privacy is critically important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how Travooz ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, discloses, and safeguards your information when you use our website, mobile application, and related services (collectively, the "Service").
By using our Service, you agree to the collection and use of your information in accordance with this policy. The personal information we collect is used to provide and improve the Service, personalize your travel experience, and communicate with you. We will not use or share your information with anyone except as described in this Privacy Policy.
The terms used in this Privacy Policy have the same meanings as in our Terms and Conditions, which are accessible on our website, unless otherwise defined here.
1. Information We Collect and Use
For a better experience and to provide our travel services, we may require you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information. The information we collect can be categorized as follows:
•	Personal Identifiers: This includes your name, email address, phone number, and postal address.
•	Travel and Booking Information: This includes passport details, date of birth, nationality, travel itinerary, flight information, hotel preferences, rental car information, and emergency contact details.
•	Payment Information: We collect payment card details, billing address, and other financial information necessary to process your transactions. This data is processed directly by our secure, PCI-compliant third-party payment processors.
•	Location Information: We may collect precise or approximate location information from your mobile device to provide location-specific services, such as finding nearby hotels, attractions, or airport services. You can enable or disable location services through your device settings.
•	Device and Technical Information: We automatically collect information from your device, including your IP address, operating system, browser type, app version, and unique device identifiers. This data is used for analytics, service improvement, and fraud prevention.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect for various purposes, including:
•	To create and manage your account.
•	To process your travel bookings, reservations, and payments.
•	To provide customer support and respond to your inquiries.
•	To send you booking confirmations, travel itineraries, and important service updates (e.g., flight changes).
•	To personalize your experience and suggest relevant travel options.
•	To conduct analytics and improve our Service, features, and content.
•	To detect, prevent, and address technical issues and fraudulent activities.
•	To comply with legal obligations.
3. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
Our Service uses "cookies" and similar tracking technologies to track activity on our Service and hold certain information. Cookies are files with a small amount of data that are sent to your browser from our website and stored on your device.
We use both session and persistent cookies for the following purposes:
•	Essential Cookies: To enable core functionality and secure areas of our site.
•	Performance/Analytics Cookies: To understand how visitors use our site and improve their experience.
•	Functionality Cookies: To remember your preferences and settings.
•	Advertising Cookies: To deliver tailored advertisements and track the effectiveness of our marketing campaigns.
You have the option to accept or refuse these cookies through your browser settings. If you choose to refuse our cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of our Service.
4. Service Providers
We may employ third-party companies and individuals ("Service Providers") for the following reasons:
•	To facilitate our Service (e.g., cloud hosting providers).
•	To provide the Service on our behalf (e.g., payment processors, airlines, hotels, and car rental agencies).
•	To perform Service-related services (e.g., customer support, email delivery).
•	To assist us in analyzing how our Service is used (e.g., Google Analytics).
These third parties have access to your Personal Information only to perform these tasks on our behalf and are legally obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.
5. International Data Transfers
As an online travel agency, your information may be transferred to — and maintained on — computers located outside of your state, province, country, or other governmental jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ. By using our Service, you consent to such transfer. We will take all steps reasonably necessary to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
6. Data Security
We value your trust in providing us with your Personal Information and strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect it. We implement a variety of security measures, including encryption and access controls. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we work to protect your data, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
7. Children’s Privacy
Our Services are not directed to anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will immediately delete it from our servers. If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.
8. Your Rights and Choices
Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal data, such as the right to access, correct, or delete the personal data we hold about you. You can also opt-out of marketing communications at any time by using the "unsubscribe" link in our emails or by contacting us directly.
9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date. We will also provide a more prominent notice, such as an email notification, for material changes. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
10. Contact Us
If you have any questions, concerns, or suggestions about our Privacy Policy or our data practices, please do not hesitate to contact us at:
Email: info@travooz.com
We will aim to respond to all legitimate inquiries within a reasonable timeframe.

